  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study aims to compare the efficacy and satisfaction of blood glucose management between&#xD;
      continuous glucose monitoring versus traditional self blood glucose measurement in diabetic&#xD;
      patients after pancreatectomy.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be enrolled after the 75g oral glucose tolerance test performed 7 days after&#xD;
      pancreatectomy. Patients will be divided into two groups by randomization (continuous glucose&#xD;
      measurement method vs. traditional self blood glucose measurement method), and 3months after&#xD;
      surgery, HbA1c, hypoglycemic events, and satisfaction would be compared.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
